filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, you did it!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Would you like to cut the umbilical cord?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, that's spongy.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I know. He has your eyes.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I mean, I know that's not possible, but he does.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: We'll just get him cleaned up a bit.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I'm really happy for you guys.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: How do you feel?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I'm tired!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, you don't have that much time to relax. The other one will be along in a minute.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I... I'm sorry, who should be along in a what now?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: The next baby should be along in a minute.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: We only ordered one!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You know it's twins, right?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, yeah! These are the faces of two people in the know!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I can't believe you didn't know it's twins! This has never happened before.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, gosh. That makes me feel so special and good.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, it's here in the paperwork we got from the clinic in Ohio.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I don't think so. Although, they did mention something about two heartbeats. But I thought that was just mine and the baby's. They kept saying both heartbeats are really strong, and I thought well, that's good 'cause I'm having a baby.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: This is unbelievable.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Twins actually run in my family.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What do we do?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What do you mean "what do we do"?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Chandler, you're panicking!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Uh-huh! Join me, won't you?! Okay, what do you say we keep one, and then just like have an option on the other one?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: We can't split them up!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Why not? We could give each of them half a medallion, and then years later, they'll find each other and be reunited. I mean, that's a great day for everybody.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, what if the person who adopts the other one is horrible?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What if they're not? What if it's adopted by a king?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, because I hear the king is looking to adopt.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Monica, we are not ready to have two babies!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: That doesn't matter! We have waited so long for this. I don't care if it's two babies. I don't care if it's three babies! I don't care if the entire cast of "Eight is Enough" comes out of there! We are taking them home, because they are our children!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: It looks like we're about ready over here.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Come on, Erica, start pushing again now.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Ow!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Here she comes!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: And then she said it was the perfect way to say goodbye.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God! What did you say?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Nothing! What do you say to that?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Ross, you've got to tell her how you feel!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No way!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You can't just give up! Is that what a dinosaur would do?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Dude, I'm just trying to speak your language.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Ross, Rachel doesn't know that you wanna get back together. If she did, she might feel differently. She might not even go.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You really think so?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hi!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Can't a girl finish a song around here?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hi! So I just dropped Emma off at my mom's.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, you're not taking her with you tonight?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No, we decided that I would go ahead and set up first, and then my mom would bring Emma to Paris on Sunday.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Wow, eight hour flight with a one-year old? Good luck, mom.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Are you kidding? Eight hours with my mother talking about Atkins? Good luck, Emma!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Alright, you know what? You're right. I should at least tell her how I feel.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Ross, wait!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What? What?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Could you get me a muffin?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Rachel?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I... I know you're leaving tonight, but I just have to tell you. I love you.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I... I don't know if that changes your plans at all, but I thought you should know.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh... Bye guys.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Unbelievable!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey, you know what might help?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I'm not getting you a muffin!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Do you think they recognize each other from in there?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Maybe. Unless they're like two people who have lived in apartments next to each other for years, and then one day they're pushed through a vagina and they meet.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: We're going to take Erica to recovery now.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: There's something that we wanna tell you. We decided to name the girl-baby Erica.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God, that's just like my name!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Son of a gun, it is!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Anyway, I'm gonna go and get some rest. I'm really glad I picked you guys. You're gonna make great parents. Even Chandler.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, well, bye!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Bye!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Bye!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: We'll call you!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Have fun at church-camp!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, look at these little bunnies!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I know! You ready to trade?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Alright, let's see..

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: We could trade later.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, I'm good.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey, what are you working on?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: It's a... It's a "welcome home" sign for the baby.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: How sweet! Oh, is that the baby?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No, I sat in the paint.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey. So, did you talk to Rachel?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No, and I'm not going to.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Why not?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Because she's just going to shoot me down. You guys saw what happened with Gunther. That did not look like fun.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: How can you compare yourself to Gunther? I mean, sure, he's sexy in a more obvious way. You have a relationship with her, you slept together last night.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, and she still wants to go! It's pretty clear where she is.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, I know what you mean. I mean, sometimes...

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Uh, Joe?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Damn it!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Look, even if I were gonna tell her, I don't have to do it now. Okay? I'll be seeing her again. We've got time.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No, you don't! She's going to Paris! She is going to meet somebody. Do you know how many hot guys there are in Paris? It's... It's a city of Gunthers!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey! What do you have there?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, I made a little something. If I had more time to work on it, it'd be better, but..

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God! You did that yourself?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Honey, that's gorgeous!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You know, the baby can't read, Mike!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hi! You guys, the car-service just got here. I can't believe they're not home yet! I have to catch my stupid plane. I wanna see the baby!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Monica just called from the cab. She said they should be here any minute. And apparently, there's some big surprise.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, did she sound happy about it? 'Cause my friend Ethel's baby was born with a teeny, tiny beard.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hi! Oh my gosh!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What... What...

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, okay, awkward question. The hospital knows you took two, right?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yes, it's twins!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, they're so cute! Now, what, what kinds are they?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Her name is Erica.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Aw..

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey, that pregnant girl's name was Erica.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah. It's a shame you two didn't get to spend more time together.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, we named the boy Jack after dad.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Aw, he's gonna be so happy.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, Jack Bing. I love that. Ooh, it sounds like a '40s newspaper guy, you know? "Jack Bing, Morning Gazette. I'm gonna blow this story wide open!"

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my gosh. Wow, so beautiful.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh yeah? Well, tell me which one, and I'll try slip it in my coat.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Seriously. Wanna make one of those?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: One? How about a whole bunch?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Really?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah! Ooh, we could teach them to sing, and we can be like the Von Trapp family! Only without the Nazis. Although that sounds kinda dull.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, you guys, I can't believe this. But I'll leave now, or I'm gonna miss my plane.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I'm just so glad you got to see the babies.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Me too. Oh, I'm just sorry I'm not gonna be around to watch you two attempt to handle this! Alright, I can't say goodbye to you guys again. I love you all so much.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I love you.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I love you.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Call us when you get there.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I will. Ross, come here.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I just want you to know.. Last night.. I'll never forget it.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Neither will I.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Alright, now I really have to go. Okay. Au revoir! Oh, they're gonna really hate me over there.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: So, you just let her go?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey, maybe that's for the best.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah. You know? You just... Look, you gotta... You gotta think about last night the way she does, okay? Maybe, maybe sleeping together was the perfect way to say goodbye?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: But now she'll never know how he feels!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Maybe now you can actually do it. You know? You can finally get over her.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, that's true. Except I don't wanna get over her.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I don't! I wanna be with her.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Really?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, I'm gonna go after her.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, you are!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Woo!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Wait, wait! Get your coat! Get your coat!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: My coat...

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: This is so cool!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I have no idea what's going on, but I am excited!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: But Ross, Ross. What do you, what do you think she's going to say?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I don't know, but I.. Look, even if she shoots me down, at least I won't spend the rest of my life wondering what would have happened. Where - where is my coat?!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You didn't bring one! My cab's downstairs, I'll drive you to the airport.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, guys, wish me luck.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hurry!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Good luck, good luck!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: There's no seatbelt!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: That's okay. If - if we hit anything, the engine will explode, so you know, it's better if you're thrown from the car.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Alright, alright, let's do this!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: 18th and East End.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I - I don't take passengers.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey! The law says you have to accept any fare.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No, you don't understand. This isn't a real cab.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Alright, I gotta report you. What's your medallion number?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: My medallion number is, "Get out of the cab!"

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Get out of the cab!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, hey, hey, can I give you guys your house-warming present now?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Now, that you can do.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Alright!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Ah... Chick Jr.? Duck Jr.? Don't hide from mama!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You can open your eyes now.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Are we off the bridge?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yes.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Is the old woman on the bicycle still alive?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yes, she jumped right back up.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God, Phoebe, slow down!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Do you wanna get to Rachel in time?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yes, but I don't wanna die in your cab!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You should have thought of that before you got in!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Toll-booth.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hurry!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Damn, that window is clean.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Quack, quack, tweet, tweet, quack, quack, tweet, tweet, quack, quack, tweet, tweet, quack, quack, tweet, tweet, quack, tweet, quack...

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: We were wondering what was taking so long with the gift, but now we understand you were doing this.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, I wanted to surprise you, but for your house-warming gift, I got you a baby-chick and a baby-duck!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Really? You got us a chick and a duck?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, great! Just what you want for a new house with infants. Bird feces.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, yeah, they must have jumped off the table, 'cause now they're gone!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, don't worry, we'll find them.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Actually, I'm gonna go check on the twins.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Alright.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh God! What did I just step on?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: It's okay, it's just an egg roll.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh..

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You stepped on my egg roll?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I'm sorry, I didn't know to look for Chinese food on the floor.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Just put it on a plate and leave.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, let's find these birds.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Alright.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Wait, wait. Do you hear that?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh! They're in the table!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, that can't be good!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: We gotta get them out of there!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: How?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, oh! Maybe we can lure them out. You know any birdcalls?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, tons, I'm quite the woodsman.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, maybe we can just tip the table a little.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Joey, wait! The ball!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh God! So what do we do?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I don't know. Maybe we can open this up somehow.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No... It's all glued together.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Does that mean we have to bust it open?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I don't know. Maybe.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I know! It's.. It's the foosball table.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: All right, you know what? We don't have a choice. It's like I would have said in that sci-fi movie if I'd gotten the part. "Those are our men in there, we have to get them out! Even if I have to sacrifice the most important thing in my life; my time-machine."

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Did that movie ever get made?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: It did not.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Ross, where are you going?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: To talk to Rachel, isn't that why we took a ride in the death-cab?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What? What are you just gonna walk up to her at the gate? Have you never chased anyone through the airport before?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Not since my cop-show got cancelled.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You have to get a ticket to get past security.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What? We're never gonna make it!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Not with that attitude! Now, haul ass!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, if you could all walk slower, that'd be great.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God! I was so afraid I wasn't gonna remember any of my high-school French, but I understood every word you just said!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, shoot. I had it. Oh, I can't believe this.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I have it, I have it, I have it. Oh, okay, I can't find it, but I remember that I was in seat 32C, because that's my bra-size.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, fine! But you know what? If I was in 36D, we would not be having this problem.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey, I need a ticket.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Just one? I drive you all the way down here, and I don't get to see how it works out?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Fine, two tickets, I need two tickets.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: We're on our honeymoon.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I don't care. Whatever is the cheapest.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I'm so lucky I married you.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh! Shoot! Damn it! Where is it? Oh! Oh! I found it! I found it!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hah! I found it! I told you I would find it! In your face! You're a different person.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, flight 421 to Paris. I don't see it, do you see it?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No, did we miss it?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No, no, no. That's impossible. It doesn't leave for another 20 minutes.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Maybe we have the flight-number wrong. God.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hello.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey, it's me. Here's Ross.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What? Hey, hey, listen..

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God! Ross, you wouldn't believe the cute little noises the twins are making. Listen.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Monica? Monica, Monica, Monica, Monica..?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, I'm sorry. Shoot, they were doing it before.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: That's alright. Listen, listen.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, wait, wait, wait! Here they go again.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Monica? Monica, Monica, Monica, Monica..?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Isn't that cute?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: That is precious! Listen! I need Rachel's flight information.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, okay. Alright, it's flight 421. Leaves at 8:40.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yes, that's what I have. It's not on the board.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: That's what it says here. Flight 421, leaves at 8:40, Newark airport.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Newark airport. Why, where are you?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: JFK.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: And we're also gonna buy you tiny, bird hearing-aids.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay. Here goes.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What's the matter?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I need to say goodbye to the table first.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I understand.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay. Table, you have given us so many great times. And you guys, Jordan, Victor, Joel... All of you guys. What can I say? You guys make us look good. You wanna say anything?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, here we go. I can't do it.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, I can't do it either.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey! Did you find them?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, they're stuck inside the table!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: We have to bust it open, but neither of us can do it!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, well sure. This gotta be so hard. I'll do it. Gimme!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Phoebe! Wow! No, no, no!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, I've never gone this fast before.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Phoebe, forget it, okay? Newark is - is like an hour away. There's no way we're gonna make it in time.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: She's got her cell, you could call her.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I am not doing this over the phone.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You don't have any other choice!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hello?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Rachel? Oh, good. Hey, by the way, did you just get on the plane?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yay.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Uh, Rach, hang on.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Phoebe? Is everything okay?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Uhm, actually no. No, you've... You have to get off the plane.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What? Why?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I have this feeling that something's wrong with it. Something is wrong with the left Philange.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, honey, I'm sure there's nothing wrong with the plane.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Alright, look, I have to go. I love you, and I will call you the minute I get to Paris.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, that was just my crazy friend. She told me I should get off the plane, because she had a feeling that there was something wrong with the left Philange.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I wouldn't worry about it. She's always coming up with stuff like this, and you know what? She's almost never right.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well...

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Wait, what are you doing?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Could I get some peanuts?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: This is ridiculous! I...

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, okay.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Alright. My job here is done.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: That was... Impressive.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, you didn't even use the tools for most of it!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, they were just slowing me down. Alright, I have to get back to the babies. I'll see you girls later.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Sorry about the table, man.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You gonna buy a new one?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Probably not. Nah. I don't know how much I'm gonna wanna play after you go.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, at least we got these little guys out.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Aww, we were worried about you! Hm. I guess I better get used to things crapping in my hand, huh?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I'm gonna miss these little guys. It was nice having birds around again.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey, you know what? Maybe we should keep them here with you.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, I mean we've got a lot going on right now. And, plus, here they'd have their own room.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I could get a goose!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You know, I - I think you're set with the poultry.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Thanks man. Did you hear that, you guys? You're gonna get to stay here! And, and it's good, you know, 'cause, 'cause now you have a reason to come visit.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I think there may be another reason. So, awkward hug or lame cool guy handshake?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Uh, lame cool guy handshake, yeah.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Where is she?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I don't see her.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Rachel! Rachel Green!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: There she is!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Rachel! Rachel!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No, no, I just have to talk to someone.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No, no, no, but...

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God... What.. What are you guys doing here?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, you're on.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What? What? Ross, you're scaring me. What's going on?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, the thing is..

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Don't go.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Please, please stay with me. I am so in love with you. Please, don't go.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I know, I know. I shouldn't have waited 'till now to say it, but I'm.. That was stupid, okay? I'm sorry, but I'm telling you now. I love you. Do not get on this plane.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey, hey. I know you love me. I know you do.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I - I have to get on the plane.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No, you don't.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yes, I do.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No, you don't.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: They're waiting for me, Ross. I can't do this right now, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Rachel?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I'm so sorry.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I really thought she'd stay.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I'm sorry.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, that's it. Everything's packed.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Wow, this is weird.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I know.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah. Uh, does this mean there's nothing to eat?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I put three lasagnas in your freezer.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I love you!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: So did you guys make it in time?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, yeah, he talked to her, but she got on the plane anyway.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Where's Ross?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: He went home. He didn't want to see anybody.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Let her off the plane!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Try to understand!

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No! No! Oh my God. Did she get off the plane? Did she get off the plane?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I got off the plane.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You got off the plane.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I do love you.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I love you too, and I'm never letting you go again.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay. 'Cause this is where I wanna be, okay? No more messing around. I don't wanna mess this up again.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Me neither, okay? We are - we're done being stupid.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay. You and me, alright? This is it.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: This is it. Unless we're on a break.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Don't make jokes now.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, please be careful with that. It was my grandmother's. Be careful.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: If that falls off the truck, it wouldn't be the worst thing.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Wow.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I know. It seems smaller somehow.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Has it always been purple?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey, do you realise that at one time or another we all lived in this apartment?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, yeah, that's true.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Uh, I haven't.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Wait a minute. What about that summer during college that you lived with grandma, and you tried to make it as a dancer?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Do you realise we almost made it ten years without that coming up?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, honey, I forgot. I promised Treeger that we'd leave our keys.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, okay.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: So, I guess this is it.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah. I guess so.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, it's gonna be okay.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: We got some time.

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, should we get some coffee?

filename: S10E17-S10E18 The Last One Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Sure. Where?
Treeger’s snaking the shower drain.
Maybe he found you flip-flop.
Hey!
Whoa! Is this porn? What did I do? I must’ve hit something on the remote.
Do we pay for this?
No, we didn’t even pay our cable bill—maybe this is how they punish us.
Maybe we shouldn’t pay our phone bill—free phone sex.
Yeah, Joey just pressed something on the remote and it just, came on!
Like finding money with naked people on it!
We don’t know what could make this go away.
Yeah, so no one touches the remote. And no one touches the TV!
And no one touches the air around the TV!
Imagine a protective porn bubble if you will, okay?
Well at least, I’m going to mute it.
We still have porn.
Hey.
Hi!
Honey, what are you doing? That’s too heavy.

All right, then show me some manly moves.
All right.
I don’t know how to lead.
Hello.
Hi.
We’d like to close our accounts.
No-no.
No, we’d just like to close them.
I wanna quit the bank!
Oh wow! That was amazing, was that really just an hour?!
Yeah! In… really long hour world.
What?
Ugh, okay, I have an enormous crush on you. But because you’re a client, I can’t ask you out, even though you give me y’know, the feeling.
Wow! I had no idea! But you know, I could always find another masseuse.
Really?!
Yeah, really.
What?
Suddenly, I very aware that I’m naked.
Oh yeah, oh and I know, but this isn’t what it looks like, ‘cause Rick is my ahh, husband.
Yes, I will tell her.
So you didn’t leave the bank?
No! And somehow, we ended up with a joint checking account.
What are you ever gonna use that for?!
To pay for the gym.
Hey.
Hey! So I had a great day, Rick and I really hit it off, and we started making out, and then my boss walked in and fired me for being a whore.
What?!
You got fired?!
Oh my Gosh!
It’s so weird, I have never been fired from anything before!
Sweety...

I just-I just started walking around not knowing what to do next, y’know? I-I started asking people on the street if they wanted massages. Then these policemen, thought I was a whore too. It’s been a really bad day, whore wise.
Yeah… Bunny-rabbit.
Look, you wanna use our place?
We did it!!
I know, it was amazing! I mean, we totally nailed it, it was beautiful.
Oh well, okay, good luck.
Unless you wanna practice the Foxtrot again? Or-or the Tango?
Okay.
Go get ‘em Treeger.
No, I’m good.
So it looks like you’ve got some great experience here. Let’s see ahh, reason for leaving last job?
Yeah, they thought I was a whore.
Okay, we’ll give a call if anything comes up.
Great! Thank you very much.
Are you sure you wanna do this?
Whoa!
Oh my God!
Oh my God!! Is everybody getting married?!!
Hey!
Hey!
What are you guys doing here?
Ross and Rachel left us a message saying they were getting married! Isn’t that why you guys are here?
Yes! Well that-yes.
Why else would we be here?
Well! What happened?! Did we miss it?
We actually missed it.
This is insane!
What’s the big deal, y’know? It’s not like it’s a real marriage.
What?!
Yeah, if you get married in Vegas, you’re only married in Vegas.
What are you talking about? If you get married in Vegas you’re married everywhere.
Yeah!
Oh my God!—Eh! Well…
Why are we in bed together?
I don’t know. Do-do you have any clothes on?
Really?!
No! But we-we didn’t have…sex-uh, did we? I mean, I don’t remember much about last night, it was such a blur.
Oh! I remember laughing! I laughed a lot.
And we didn’t have sex.
Ohh, I mean, we were really drunk. I’m just glad we didn’t do anything stupid.
Oh Joey, I’m so sorry. You want some of my breakfast?
Nah, I’m too depressed to eat. I’ll probably eat in like 5 minutes. So I guess I’ll just fly home with you guys, what time’s your flight?
What about my cab?
I don’t need that anymore.
No, Joey! You borrowed my cab; you have to drive it back.
I don’t know, it’s such a long trip.
It’ll be great! We-we could talk, and play games! Huh? This could be our chance to like renew our friendship.
Are you asking me to have a frenaissance?
Sure?
All right. Although I don’t think we need one, I never stopped loving you.
Hi!
Hey.
Hey.
So, has anyone talked to Dr. and Mrs. Geller yet?
Um-hmm, yeah. They left me a message; they should be here any minute.
Where is the waitress?! I’m starving!
It’s a buffet man.
Listen, I gotta talk to you.
Monica and I almost got married last night.

Look, I just don’t think Monica and I are ready to get married yet! Y’know? I mean, I love her and everything but seeing Ross and Rachel coming out of that chapel was like a, like a wake-up call that Monica and I are moving so fast. Y’know? And, how do I tell her without crushing her?
Oh! Tell her she’s not marriage material.
What?!
Girls say it to me all the time! And believe me, if she’s anything like me, she’s just gonna be relieved.
How do I tell Chandler that it’s too soon. It’s gonna break his heart, he’s not gonna think that I don’t love him anymore.
Well you don’t.
Yes I do!
Good! Good! I was just testing you.
Oh hi! Hi! Y’know, we were just talking about bacon.
No, we were talking about tennis. Tennis is more believable.
Hey!
Hey!
What?
Are we gonna talk about what you guys did last night? Or…
Yeah!
Uh-huh! Ross invited us all to watch.
Rach! We weren’t gonna miss our friends getting married!
What?! Hello! We didn’t get married.
No, we didn’t get married! That’s ridiculous!
We-we-we—I remember being in a chapel.
Oh my God.
I—They would not let us get married when we were that drunk!
No!
They let you get married when you’re drunk! Most people who get married in Vegas are drunk!
What are you guys gonna do?
Well, I think, I think, Ross already has one. Now, this one’s free, right? Because you paid for the first two, so the third one’s free.
Laugh it up, but the joke’s on you. Because we don’t need to get divorced, okay? We we’re just gonna get an annulment.
An annulment? Ross! I don’t think surgery’s the answer here.
Oh-oh, that’s your thing.
What?
You’re thing. You’re thing. Y’know? You’re the guy who gets divorced.
Oh yeah!
No-no, that’s-that’s not my thing! I do not love getting divorced!
So, what do you think we should do?
I don’t know. But I-I-I know I love you!
So where are we on the whole going back to the place where they have all the marriages thing? I love you.
That’s a good question. Look umm, last night we let the dice decide. Maybe we should leave it up to fate again. I love you!
All right, eight we get married, but 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 9, 10, 11, 12 we don’t get married.
Sounds great.
Coming in, we got a shooter! Money please.
Ready?
Ready!
Wow! I can’t believe I actually rolled an eight.
That was so unlikely. Well, let’s get married! I guess.
Wait a minute. That wasn’t a hard eight! Last night I rolled a hard eight.
That’s right! It was the wrong kind of eight, no wedding! Damnit!

Well, you promised me a fun road trip! We’ve been on the road six hours and you’ve been asleep for five and a half! We are switching at the next rest stop and you are going to drive all the way back! That will be your punishment, you greedy sleeper!
All right. All right.
Yeah! And until then you are going to sing to me because the radio’s broken and you are selfish but have a nice voice.
Really? I don’t…
Sing!!
Hey!
Hey, hubby!
Yeah. Yeah, actually um, I wanted to talk to you about that whole annulment thing?
Uh-huh.
Okay! So, we’ll just stay married.
Yes, exactly!
And I will make everyone call me Mrs. Geller!
Wow! This is so amazing. I uh, I really thought I’d have to talk you into this more.
Okay, see now I’m scared because I don’t actually think you’re kidding.
I’m-I’m not kidding. Look I-I, I can’t have three failed marriages. I can’t. Okay? I-I am not gonna be that guy!
What-wh-what so we’ll just stay married forever?!
Okay, look, how is this gonna affect you? Really? I mean you fill some form out once and a while and instead of checking the box that says Ms you check the box that says Mrs.! It’s right next to it!

Ohh, okay, I’m sorry. You’re right. Y’know what? We absolutely can stay married, because I was under the impression that the boxes were far away from each other. All right, look, just please, take a moment here and think about what you’re asking of me.
I’m asking you to do me a favor.
You are asking me to be your wife!
And as my wife I think you should grant me this favor.
That kid really kicked me hard on the plane.
Well you did pull his hair.
He took my snack!
I’m not getting into this again!
Okay! Oh God, y’know what? It’s really bad.
This doesn’t mean anything, does it?
No!
Okay.
Don’t you think I asked him that before he got in?!
No!
Do you like car games?
Yeah, y’know the license plate game?
I love the license plate game!
Ooh, I’ll play! I’ll play!
Hey!
Hey!
I don’t know if it’s true.
Oh b-b-but it is!
Oh, okay, y’know what this is? This is a difference of opinion. And when that happens in a marriage...
Oh Ross, come on! This is not, this is not a marriage!! This is the world’s worst hangover! Ross, listen, if you do not get this annulment, I will!
All right. All right, I’ll do it.
Wait! Wait! There is the train station!
Oh, okay.
This is where I get off. Well, I have your address and phone number.
And I have your name and the fact that you’re a drifter, so the ball’s pretty much in your court.
Stop it! Stop it no! That’s not fair! Y’know I can’t resist that beautiful voice!

Pheebs, I am so sorry! I know I promised you a fun road trip with your friend and I didn’t deliver. But-but-but now I know that you think being awake is an important part of friendship! So, so, so I will strive to-to stay awake for as long as I know you.
You can still sleep at night and stuff.
Well, thank you. So, can we play 20 Questions now? I’ve got a really good one! I’ve been thinking about it since Kansas.
Okay. Is it a kind of hot sandwich?
Yes.
Is it a meatball sub?
That is incredible! You are the master!
Huh, that’s funny. You look like you’re gonna be the…
No, don’t say it! Don’t even think it!
All right, should we just, should we just get married? Y’know? I mean should we just do it? All the signs are telling us to do it.
I’m sick of the signs! It’s too fast, I’m happy the way things are!
Me too!
I don’t want things to change! Do you?
No!
All right then, then nothing changes! Everything is great! Everything stays the same! And you go unpack because it’s been three days and it’s driving me insane!
Then all your stuff would be here.
Well, what if all my stuff was here?
Then you’d be going back and forth all the time, I mean it doesn’t make any sense.
Okay. What if we lived together and you understand what I’m saying?
Live together? There have been no signs for that.
Me asking is kind of a sign.
Okay!!!!!
Yes! Okay! Okay! Wait-wait-wait!
Okay.
Oh thanks.
Here’s your key. All right, you have to christen it! Now, go out and come back in!
Ready!
Okay, a little problem. The key broke in the lock and I can’t get in!
Wait! Oh my God! I can’t get out!
This is not a sign!
No, it’s not a sign! It’s a very old key!
It’s an old key!
Oh my God it’s old!
I love you!
I love you!
Are you hugging the door right now.
No.
Yeah-yeah, me neither.
Hey!
Hey, so did everything go all right with the annulment?
Oh, yeah, no problems. It’s all taken care of.
Ross, thank you. Hey, do you guys wanna go see a movie?
Oh yeah, why not?
Pheebs?
No thanks, I’ve already seen one.
Always.
I didn’t get the annulment.
What?!
What are you doing?
The key’s stuck in the lock.
I’m not finished.
Oh.
Nice job Joe! You’re quite the craftsmen.
You look cute in bubbles.
Ehh, you're just liquored up.
Hey, it's me! I'm comin' in!
I've had a very long, hard day.
Ahh, I'm gonna go get some chicken. Want some?
Ahh, no thanks. No chicken, bye-bye then.
Okay.
You sure? Some extra crispy? Dirty rice? Beans?
For the last time no! Get out! Get out, Joey!
All right!
Are you okay? I'm so sorry, he wouldn't leave. He kept asking me about chicken.
Chicken? I could eat some chicken.
Hey Joe!
Yeah, can I get a 3-piece, some cole slaw, some beans, and a Coke-(Yelps in
Hey, Pheebs!
Mornin' Pheebs!
I have to tell you this story. Okay, I was coming over here and this driver…
What?
Oh, he was this cab driver we had in London.
Oh. Ha-ha-ha. All right, anyway…
Wait, what that place, that pub he took us too?
Uh, The Wheatsheaf.
Yeah-yeah-yeah, and they had that beer! That uh…
Bodington's!
Ooh! Ahh, Pheebs, was gonna tell a story.
Yeah, so, he had a really funny hat—I don't want to talk about it.
Hey!
Hey, Ross, Bodington's!
That was good beer.
Ohh…
Y'know, I'd walk back to London for another frosty one of those bad boys.
Y'know, I think they have those at that British pub near the trade center.
Isn't Rachel supposed to be back by now?
Oh, so-so you talked to her. Did she, did she sound mad?
No, but she likes me. You abandoned her on a plane to Greece.

Okay, I did not abandon Rachel! Okay? Emily showed up at the airport! I had to go after her! I mean, I-I did what I had to do! She's my wife! Rachel is my wife! Y'know—Emily! Emily, is my wife! Man, what is that?
So you still hadn't heard from Emily?
No, not since I lost her at the airport.
I can't believe she can out run you man!
Rach, Rach, I am so sorry. I am so-so sorry.
Oh Ross, come on! You just did what you had to do.
That's it? You're not mad? I mean, it must've been terrible.
So, what? That's it?
Well, yeah! We're cool. Totally cool.
Oh no, you're the best.
Oh, Ross, when you make out card; be sure to make it out to, EM-I-LY.
Rach, that's great! It's so good that you had a good time in Greece!

What?! I didn't have a good time in Greece! Ross abandoned me! Okay, I couldn't get a plane out, so I had to stay in their honeymoon suite with people coming up to me all the time going, "Oh, Mrs. Geller, why are you crying?" I mean, it was sooo humiliating. I felt like such an idiot! I mean, it's all my fault! And you know why, because I make very bad decisions.
Oh that's not true.
Yes it is! It is true! I went, I went after Ross in stupid London.
London is stupid! Stupid!
Phoebe, you were right. I should've never gone to London, and from now on you make all of my decisions for me.
Oh… No, I did that for someone once and I'm not comfortable having that kind of power and control over someone's life.
I'll do it!
That's fine. So Monica, you are now in control of my love life.
Okay, I gotta go to work.
And uh, Rachel, glad to have you back.
Oh, Rachel, sweetie, look, here's a really cute picture of Joey and you at the reception.
Honey, sweetie, by the edges.
…I mean it's my fault.
Sweetie! Edges! Fingers! Smudgey! Pictures!
Okay. That's okay. I-I know that you're very upset right now. I know, I know that wasn't about me.
Yeah, I guess Gunther is kinda…
Oh, I don't know. I don't know.
You're going to talk to him! Y'know what? We made a deal, I make your decisions and I say you're going to talk to him.
All right, you're the boss. I guess I gotta do what you tell me.
Hey!
Hey, Pheebs!
All right, y'know what, we've been talking about London too much haven't we?
No. I'm sorry. It's just 'cause I couldn't be there. 'Cause all I ever get to do now is pregnant stuff, it just bums me out.
Sorry.
What happened?
Well, y'know, a little of this, a little of that. Got myself a date tomorrow night.
See, didn't I tell you?! You're getting over Ross already!
Well…
What took you so long?
I got caught up and work, but I'm quitting tomorrow.
Oh, good.
Probably some y'know, European good-bye thing he picked up in London.
That's not European!
Well, it felt French.
Oh God, I really had a good time!
Yeah. Umm, unless you wanna come inside?
Yeah!
Okay. Oh, uh, wait a minute, y'know what? I uh, I can't decide this. Umm, okay, just hold on a second.
Okay, yeah!
Umm, hi!
Hi.
Is Monica around? I-I have to ask her something.
She's doing her laundry.
It came in the mail today, it's uh, 72 long-stemmed red roses, one for each day that I've known and loved Emily, cut up into mulch!
Oh, honey that's awful.
Oh, it's not so bad. Monica's gonna make potpourri! I think I'm gonna go wander out in the rain for a while.
But, it's not raining.
I can't catch a break!
Yeah?
What is the matter with you?! Do you want to fall into the trap? Do you want to fall into the trap?!
Ohh! You did not drop any socks!
I just ran into Dave and he told me that you blew him off! I mean, you listen to me! Now, I'm calling the shots! I say you leave Ross alone and go get Dave! What the hell were you trying to do?
Well, ultimately, I was trying y'know, I-I wanted…tell him y'know, that I'm still in love with him.
Why? Why not?! People love to hear that!
I make the decisions, and I say no.
Well, y'know what, no, you do not make my decisions because y'know what, you're fired.
You can't fire me. I make your decisions and I say, "I'm not fired!" Ha!
Rachel!! Come on! Let me in!
Rachel locked the door.
I'll kick that door in if you give me a little sugar.
Rachel! Let me in! Rachel!
Thank you. Rachel, can I talk to you outside for a sec?
No.
I really need to talk to you.
Well, then talk!
Okay, I will. Remember that thing that we just discussed that you wanted to do?
Yes!
What thing?
I'm gonna do it.
All right, Rachel, I know-I know you think I'm crazy, please, before you tell him you love him, just-just try to find one person who thinks this is a good idea. Because I bet you, you can't.
But I…
Please!
All right, fine.
Joey, I'm in!
Pheebs! Hey Pheebs!
Uh, okay, Pheebs?
Yeah?
Umm, y'know how the other day you were talking about how you didn't get to go to London and how you were kinda feeling left out?
Yeah?
All right, well, we felt really bad about that so we decided we should all take a little trip together!
Ohh, that's so nice! How great! Well, where? Where's the trip?!
Yeah, all of us! All day!
That sucks! That's not a trip! I just came from the park! What are we gonna high five about at the stupid Central Park? "Well, it's right by my house, all right!"
I was just trying to bring a little culture to the group.
That's fine, just don't bring it in my mouth.
Hey everybody, Pheebs is here!
Phoebe!
Hey, Pheebs!
Phoebe, woo!
Okay, woo! Hi.

Okay, Pheebs, we decided the picnic idea was a little… Y'know, it didn't have any… It-it, well it blew. So, we thought, that this afternoon that we would all go away for the whole weekend to, Atlantic City!
Ooh, Atlantic City! Oh, that's a great plan! Who's plan was that?
Mine!
Wait! It was my plan.
Nooo, I said we needed a new plan.
And, I came up with Atlantic City.
Which, is the new plan!
Okay, well, why don't we all meet upstairs in an hour?
Okay! Ooh-ahh, I'm gonna go pack. I'm gonna go pack my ass off!
Come on Rach, let's go.
Yeah, y'know what? I'm-I'm gonna meet you upstairs in a minute.
No! Rachel, you didn't find anyone so you can't tell him.
Well, y'know what, that doesn't matter.
Okay, Rachel, do you have any idea how painful it is to tell someone that you love them and not have them say it back?
Yeah, I-I don't care.
What 'cha readin'?
The paper.
Yeah, what's it about?
Events from around the globe.

Okay. Uhh, Ross, y'know what, there's something that I-that I have to talk to you about and everybody's saying that I shouldn't tell you, but I think they're wrong. I mean, and you know how people can be wrong.
Sure. Once, at work I-I thought carbon dating was fossilized…
Okay, Ross, I'm really trying to tell you something here.
Yeah.
Okay.
Go ahead.
Wow. Umm… Huh… I'm-I'm not sure what to do with that right now.
What? What? Was that a joke? 'Cause it's mean.
Why are you laughing?
Well, well I am married. Even though I haven't spoken to my wife since the wedding.
Oh God, ohh, okay, y'know what, do you think ah, do you think that you just forget that I told you this?
Well, I kinda half to. I mean, because the thing is…
The thing is y'know, that you're married to Emily.
That is what the thing is.
Ross, things aren't gonna be weird between us, right? I mean was that just the stupidest thing, me telling you that?
No. No. No, I'm-I'm glad you did. Look, if nothing else, it's-it's always great when someone tells you they love you.
No thank you for… Thank you.
Okay, let's go!
Atlantic City!
Atlantic City, baby! Let's roll some bones! Hey Joey, high-five for rolling bones!
Uh, Pheebs, you're leaking?
Oh my God! You're water broke!
Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa! Wait-wait!
Pheebs! We have to take you to the hospital now!
Pheebs, Pheebs, the babies are coming now.
I can't believe Phoebe's gonna have her babies!
I know, it's beautiful. Amazing.
Y'know what else I can't believe? I had to kiss Phoebe and Rachel every time I left a room, I mean it's too bad they didn't see us having sex.
Do you know anything about women?
No.
That's all right.

Well, of course not for tonight. Yeah, hi!

But I...

All right.

Monica, I think you've gone over to the bad place.
Hola! Hello. Hello?

Definitely.

Yay!
No, no, no, no. Tick, tick, tick, tick.

I'm not gonna gooo.

Well, ever since I was humiliated and yelled at in front of my friends, I'm just, I don't know, not in a museum benefitty kind of mood.

I'm not mad.
No.

Your not going.
Right.

Um, hum.

No.
No, because your not upset.
Right.
About the yelling.
Right, and the humiliating.
Oh, well of course, the humiliating. So, so wee, we're okay.
Um, hum.
We're good.
Right.
Okay. Honey?
Is it wrong that I was totally aroused by that?
Okay, buddy-boy. Here it is. You hide my clothes, I'm wearing everything you own.

You know what I don't care. The only person I cared about getting dressed, is the one person that says she's not even gonna go. Look Rach, I'm sorry. Okay. Look, I-I wa, I was a jerk. Oh, it’s gonna be fine.
Okay Rachel, I can’t wait to live with you! And you know what we should do? Bring Monica and then we could all live there together! We’ll have so much fun!!
But honey, I think she’s moving in with Chandler.
Oh that’s right. You’re still set on that?
Hey!
What’s wrong?
Ross and I were helping the girls pack, took a little break, I lost $1,500 to him in Cups!

The same way you lost. I started out with a King and a Queen, bamn! Ross gets a 2 and a 3. Then I get a Jack and a King, boom! Ross gets a 4 and a 5! Ross was getting the Cup card, the D-Cup, the Sittin’ Down Bonus! Meanwhile, I didn’t even get half a cup! Nothin’!!

Okay.
I’m really gonna miss you.
Thanks.
Yeah.
Yeah.
Bye house!
Bye Mon.
Bye.
She really left.
Thank you.

At a fake game!!
