filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What’s-what’s going on?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: The guys across the hall are throwing water balloons at us.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, you have to call the police! That’s what I did to the kids in my building!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No, it’s a water balloon fight! We started it!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, sure.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Uh, so this play umm, what do you think? It’s-it’s gotten great reviews! Y’know the uh…

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Ugh! So close!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey you guys! Look!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I got me some drinks!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What are you doing?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Open bar!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well now it’s an empty bar.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You just can’t stand anyone else enjoying themselves can’t you?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I won! That was my guess!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What?! What?! What?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I guessed 20,000!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Joey! It is an auction! You don’t guess, you buy!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What?! I don’t have 20,000!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Forget her! You enjoy this!! (Pulls him back up and starts applauding again. Joey waves and does a salute.]

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What are you doing?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Are you okay?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yes! Yes! I’m good! Are you good? Are you good? Is everything—are you—are you perrr-perfect?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah. I’m okay. I’m actually—I’m a little cold, can I have your jacket?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yes! I’m fine. In fact I’ve been fine for a long time now and I think, the reason is you.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Ohh that’s sweet!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay umm, before I meant you I had really little life and I couldn’t imagine growing old with…

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh God, maybe he won’t see us. Richard!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey, it’s good to see you!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You too, you let uh, your hair grow long.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah—Oh that’s right. You, you always wanted me too. Hey, I see you got your mustache back.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, my nose got lonely.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hi.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Chandler, wh-why don’t we sit down?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh. Good to see you guys.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What were you thinking?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I didn’t know it was an auction!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Wh?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I figured, take a guess, help a charity, free boat!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Why would a charity give away a free boat?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I don’t know! Charity?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Ugh!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Phoebe, don’t you think you’ve had enough to drink?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I’m just helping the kids!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: How is you drinking helping the kids?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Because the more I drink, the less there is for the kids to drink.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh hi!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Just out of curiosity, how-how much is that boat worth?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, what am I gonna do Rach?! I don’t have that kind of money!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Look, I don’t know why the kids need a youth center anyway! Y’know? They should just watch TV after school like I did and I turned out fine!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Not great.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: And so, we’re hiding in the bathroom.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: And-and then I sneak out and before Monica can her parents come in.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: So I hide in the shower and the next thing you know they’re going at it right on the bathroom floor.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I got a good one, I got a good one! I once walked in on both my parents making love to the same guy.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Ohh.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Who?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Richard!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh you knew that. Good!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I thought you were going out with Elizabeth.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, I was but uh, she was a little busy with a water balloon fight.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh Ross, sometimes grown-ups have commitments they just can’t get out of!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Y’know, maybe she is too young for me. Y’know, when I was over there and she was running around with her friends, I felt like I was a baby-sitter. I finally started to see what you guys were talking about. I don’t know what to do.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay umm, bad stuff. Well, I’m-I’m 12 years older than she is.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: If the school finds out you’re fired.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hmm.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: She’s leaving for three months.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: For camp!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, good stuff. Umm, well she’s-she’s sweet and pretty and…

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No! No! I…didn’t do that. It’s just… Okay, honestly no. I don’t, I don’t see a big future with her.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay well I think…that’s your answer.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I’ve got to talk to her. Ugh, I hate this part.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey, you have to forget about Elizabeth. I mean if you’re not careful you may not get married at all this year!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Rach! Rachel! Okay, the next highest bidder is at table one.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh great!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, okay.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Uhh, excuse me is there a Mr. Bowmont at this table?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh well, hello. This is your lucky day Mr. Bowmont, the uh gentleman day sailer as just become available again and I believe that you made a bid of $18,000.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You-you have to pay that! It’s not just a guess.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Ohh…

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Are you kidding me?! She’s gonna this boat!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Y-Yeah! What-what is your wife’s name?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Pam! Oh God okay, just imagine this, "The Pam."

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Aw-awww!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, uh-uh imagine this, "The Mr. Bowmont."

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oooooh…

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No way! It’s mine!!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: All that stuff you just said? I want that!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: But Joey you don’t have $20,000!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Who cares?! I-I’ll make payments, whatever it takes, I want the Mr. Bowmont!!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God, you’re back!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Why do you want to see my hand?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I wanna see what’s in your hand. I wanna see the trash.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Eww! Oh, it’s all dirty. You should throw this out.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What happened?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Richard was there so I couldn’t do it!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I’m gonna do it tomorrow y’know, and-and surprise her, but now you’ve ruined it!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: We didn’t ruin it!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Who walks into a room and asks to see a person’s hands?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, a palm reader, a manicurist, a hand doctor…

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Glove salesman!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Good one! Yeah.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: This is terrible. What am I going to do?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Look, she only suspects something okay? She doesn’t know for sure, so just throw her off the track.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: That’s right, I can throw her off. I can make her think marriage is the last thing on my mind.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah! Yeah! Convince her that-that you’re scared of commitment! Convince her that you’re a little coward!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I can do that, I’ve had 30 years of practice.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: That guy’s still doing that?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No, you’re too late!!! She already took out the trash!!!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Elizabeth, thank God! I was just thinking about…

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You suck!!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay, break-up’s still on!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What are you up too?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well that’s a little crazy. Although I am y’know glad to hear that you’re branching out on what you look at on the Internet.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, well… Y’know, it just got me thinking though, why would anybody ever want to get married huh?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Why?! To celebrate your relationship! To solidify your commitment! To declare your love for one another to the world!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Eh…

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay well that’s good to know.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey Monica, there’s a customer who wants to complement the chef, should I let him in?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hi!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Richard!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Actually, I’m not here to complement the chef.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Ohh… Oh, that’s okay I hate when people come back to complement the chef. Like I have nothing better to do! So what’s up?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, it was great seeing you the other night.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, good to see you too. Did you come down here to tell me that?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What uh—What did you—What?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I still love you. And I know I probably shouldn’t even be here telling you this, I mean you’re with Chandler a guy I really like, and if you say he’s straight I’ll believe you! After seeing ya the other night I knew if I didn’t tell ya I’d regret it for the rest of my life. Letting you go was the stupidest thing I ever did.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Y’know you’re really not supposed to be back here!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well yeah, I’m sorry. I know this is the wrong time and the wrong place but I had to tell ya! I wanna spend my life with you. I wanna marry you. I wanna have kids with you.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I know this is crazy but am I too late?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What the… Yes you’re too late! Where was all this three years ago?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well I know I was an idiot! And I tried to forget you, I really did! Y’know after we had lunch last year I spent six months in Africa trying to get you out of my head!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What were you doing in Africa?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Working with blind kids.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Ohhh! What are you doing to me?! Oh look, I-I… I’m sorry but umm, this-this-this-this is not going to happen.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Okay that’s fine, I’ll walk away. And I’ll never bother you again, but only if you tell me Chandler’s willing to give you everything I am.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well he is! Yeah, I mean marriage is all he talks about! My goodness, in fact, I’m the one that’s making him wait!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You are?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Why?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Why? Because of the government.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Isn’t it incredible?! Monica and Chandler, gettin’ married.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I know, they’re gonna be so happy together.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Ohh… I mean two best friends falling in love, how often does that happen?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Not that often!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No! I’m so happy for them!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Me too! So happy for them!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I’m so happy and not at all jealous.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh no! No God, definitely not jealous!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I mean I’m probably 98% happy, maybe 2% jealous. And I mean what’s 2%? That’s nothing.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Totally. I’m like 90/10.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah me too.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey uh, have you guys scene Chandler?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: So that marriage stuff that you were saying yesterday, you don’t really believe that do you?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Sure I do. In fact, I think the whole concept of marriage is unnatural. I mean look at pigs. Let’s take a second here and look at pigs. Okay pigs don’t mate for life. I mean a pig can have like a hundred sexual partners in a lifetime, and that’s just an ordinary pig not even a pig that’s good at sports!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, but that’s pigs not people!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: If marriage worked, I’d be all for it. But do you know what the divorce rate in this country is? 97%.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Wait a minute. Are you honestly telling me that-that you may never want to get married?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, never say never but y’know probably uh yeah, never.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh my God! Then-then-then what are we even doing?! What is this?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Whoa! Whoa! Whoa! What is all this pressure?! Is this some new kind of strategy? Why don’t you put down your copy of ‘The Rules’ huh mantrap?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Y’know what?! I gotta go! Ugh!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: We’re gonna find love!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Definitely!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, I’m pretty confident about that. That’s what makes it so easy for me to be 80% happy for Monica and Chandler! It would be nice to have a little guarantee though.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What do you mean?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well y’know, some people make deals with a friend, like if neither of them are married by the time they’re 40, they marry each other.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You mean a backup?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Exactly!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, yeah I got that.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You do?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hm-mmm.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Who?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Joey.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Joey?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Are you serious?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, I locked him years ago!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Wh… So… If neither of you are married by the time you’re 40, you’re gonna marry Joey.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yep, we shook on it. Yeah but believe me that is not how he wanted to seal the deal.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, seriously?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Charming.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well hey, it’s just a backup.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey Monica!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Have you seen Rachel? Or a mirror?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: This is for my boat, pretty cool huh?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, it’s great.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Whoa-whoa, what’s the matter?! Talk to the captain!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I’m just having one of those days where you realize you’re in a dead-end relationship!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Chandler giving you a hard time huh?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: It’s not like I want to get married tomorrow! It’s just that I-I’d like to believe that I’m in a relationship that’s actually going somewhere, that I’m not just wasting my time!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Well, you know Chandler.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: No I don’t know Chandler! Not anymore! It’s like it’s like something’s changed.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Maybe you changed?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I didn’t change!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Maybe that’s the problem.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Chandler is a complex fellow, one who is unlikely to take a wife.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Is that some kind of boat talk?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What does he think? Does he think I’m just gonna wait around for nothing?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Monica face it, Chandler is against marriage. And-and always will be!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: There are?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah! Richard!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: That’s right.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Chandler loves marriage!!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You just told me that he hates marriage! That-that he’s a-a complex fellow who’s unlikely to take a wife! That-that he’s against marriage and always will be!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: You got that from what I said?!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: When the Cretaceous period ended, the dinosaurs were gone.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: What happened you guys?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Rach!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey you!

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Hey, come on in.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh thank you. Hey y’know, I’m so sorry to hear about you and Elizabeth.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Oh, thanks. Yeah, I really thought we’d be able to make it work, but uh, I guess it just wasn’t meant to be.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Yeah, love. It’s a tricky business isn’t it?

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: I guess so.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: So what do you say we make a pact? If you and I are both single by the time we’re 40, we get married. I mean, we know each other, we like each other, and we’ve-we’ve already slept together so y’know there’ll be no surprises there! You know what I mean? No like, "What’s that?!"

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Right. Ohh! You-you want me to be your backup.

filename: S06E24 The Proposal Part I  II.txt
dialogue: Exactly.

Hey, if mommy can have a wife, daddy can have a bra.
Oh, no-no-no, see, that-that clock’s a little fast, uh, we have 17 minutes. Huh, what can we do in 17 minutes? Twice?
Well that’s ambitious.
Hey, uh, you can ignore that.
That’s Carol with your son!
Uhh, believe me when he’s older, he’ll understand.
Hey, it’s so nice to finally meet you!
Me too!
Ohh, y’know, Susan’s gonna be shooting a commercial in London next week.
Oh yeah, I’m so excited, I’ve never been there.
Oh, well, I’ll show you around.
That would be great! Also, uh, I was hoping to catch a show so if you can make any suggestions…
Oh, there’s tonnes of terrific stuff—I’ll go with you!
Ahh!
Look at you two, bonding, making us late for the airport so…
Are you all right?
Oh, he’s fine. He’s fine. It’s just that us getting along is difficult for him, because he doesn’t like me.
Oh come on! That’s-that’s… true.
Hi!
Hey!
Hey! Do we have a baby name yet?
Well, it certainly worked for that Valdez kid.
Ooh-ooh, Pheebs, you want a strong name? How about, The Hulk?
No, I’m-I’m not sure about Hulk, but I like the idea of a name starting with "The."
Oh, want a good name, go with Joey. Joey’s your pal. Joey’s your buddy. "Where is everybody?" "Well, they’re hanging out with Joey."
Oh well, hey, Joey’s loveable too! But the thing about Joey is, if you need him, he’ll be there.
Well, Chandler will be there for you too. I mean, well, he might be a little late, but-but, he’ll be there. And he’ll bring you some cold soda, if want you need him for is that you’re really hot.
What do ya say? What do ya say?
I knew I shouldn’t have mentioned it! That’s what I wanted to name my kid!
Y’know what? It really creeps me out choosing other people’s sex clothes.
Sorry. I’m so exited! I’ve been waiting for this for months! I got my hair coloured! I got new sheets! I’m making him a very fancy meal.
Um-hmm.
What am I making him by the way?
Well, you’re making him a frieze salad with goat cheese and pine nuts, wild nuts, wild rice, roast asparagus, and salmon au croup.
I thought I was making him filet mignon?
Wow, I really get crabby when I cook.
Hey!
Hey!
Hey!
So uh, Emily called last night…
And now you’re giving me the message!
Turns out them Emily is just crazy about Susan. Yeah, they’re going to the theatre together! They’re going to dinner! They’re going horseback riding!
God, Susan is so fun!

Look, this is just a little too familiar, okay? For like, for like six months before Carol and I spilt up, all I heard was: "My friend Susan is so smart. My friend Susan is so funny. My friend Susan is so great."
You actually think that something can happen between Emily and Susan?
Hey, they’re going to the gym together! Two women! Stretching! Y’know they-they take a steam together! Things get a little playful—didn’t you see Personal Best?
No, but I’m gonna!
Hi! Hi! You’re crazy! Okay? This is Emily. Emily is straight.
How do you know? I mean we thought Carol was straight before I married her!
Yeah, I definitely. I don’t like the name Ross.
What a weird way to kick me when I’m down.
No! No! I-I meant for the baby!
Oh. What’s wrong with Ross?
Well, it’s just y’know that something like this would never to like The Hulk, y’know…
So, I decided I’m definitely going to go with either Joey or Chandler.
Oh! Oh-oh, you gotta pick Joey! I mean, name one famous person named Chandler.
Raymond Chandler.
Someone you didn’t make up!
Okay, there are no famous Joey’s. Except for, huh, Joey Buttafucco.
Yeah, that guy really hurt us.
Well, how about a compromise then, okay? What if it’s like y’know, Chanoey?
Okay, look, Joey! Come on, think about it, first of all, he’ll never be President. There’s never gonna be a President Joey.

All right look man, I didn’t want to bring this up, but Chandler, is the stupidest name I ever heard in my life! It’s not even a name; it’s barely even a word. Okay? It’s kinda like chandelier, but it’s not! All right? It’s a stupid, stupid non-name!
Wow, you’re, you’re right. I have a horrible, horrible name.
Okay.
So I guess it’s Joey then!
This is so nice. Thank you for doing this.
Great! Oh, it all looks sooo good!
Oh my God!
Oh I know, my God, this is so—this rice is so—I am so good.
Behind you?
Yeah, sure, okay. Okay.
All gone! So, farm birds, huh?
Yeah, it’s-it’s my only weird thing, I swear. And I-I-I would’ve told you about it, but I didn’t know they would be here.
Oh.
So, all right.
Nothing I uh, it’s just that I know that they’re still out there.
But, they’re across the hall! I mean that’s two doors away, it would take them a long time to peck their way back over here.
Okay, that’s-that’s not funny. Uhh.
Okay, y’know, would you feel better if we went someplace else? I mean we could pack all this stuff up and y’know go to your apartment.
Oh, they’re working on this week, it’s a total mess. But uh, I’m staying at my parents’ house, we could go there.
Your parents’?
Yeah, they’re out of town.
Ohh.
Yeah-yeah, it’s this huge place, and-and it’s got this gorgeous view of the park, and very, very romantic. What do you say?
Yeah that works.
They-they-they can smell fear.
Hey! How’s Ben?
Hey, Ben! Hey!
So umm, any word from Susan?
Ooh, yeah! She said she’s having sooo much fun with Emily.
Uh-huh. Uh-huh. Uh, by the by, did it uh, did it ever occur to you that, I don’t know, maybe they might be having a little too much fun?
What’s too much fun?
Y’know, the kind of fun, you and Susan had when we were married.
Oh my God, you are so paranoid!
Am I?!
Yes!
Am I?!
I can’t speak for Emily, but Susan is in a loving, committed relationship.

Uh-huh, Carol, so were we. All right, just-just imagine for a moment, Susan meets someone and-and they really hit it off. Y’know? Say-say they’re coming back from the theatre, and they-they stop at a pub for a couple of drinks, they’re laughing, y’know, someone innocently touches someone else… There’s electricity, it’s new. It’s exciting. Are you telling me there isn’t even the slightest possibility of something happening?
Maybe.
OH MY GOD!! I didn’t really believe it until you just said it!!
…and even though none of the other kids believed me, I swear to God, that duck pushed me!
Wow! This place is fabulous!
Yeah, yeah, let me show you around. This is the uh, downstairs living room.
Whoa-whoa, there’s two living rooms? God, growing up here, this place must’ve been a real babe magnet.
Yeah, well, it would’ve been, but uh, my parents just moved here.
Ohh, you should know, this place is a real babe magnet. Wanna make out?
Hey, here’s an idea. Why don’t uh, I put the food in the fridge and we can eat it later?
That sounds like a plan. Umm, is there a place I can go freshen up?
Oh yeah, yeah uh, it’s down the hall and uh, second door to your left.
Ah.
Mom, Dad, what are you guys doing here?
Umm, this may be a little weird, but I-I-I got a date here.
Oh, that-that would be great. So you didn’t even get to Italy?
Hi you!
Oh my God!
I know, I can do more than cook.
Uhh, Rachel, my parents…
Hello.
Yes!
There you go.
Well, we were going to do that after—I mean umm, next.
Oh, yeah, well… Yeah, no use wasting this baby, just lyin’ around the house.
Yes.
Dude, I am sorry about what I said!
No, no, you’re right, it is a ridiculous name!
It’s not that bad.
Yes it is! From now on, I have no first name.
So, you’re just Bing?
I have no name.
All right, so, what are we supposed to call you?
Okay uh, for now, temporarily, you can call me, Clint.
No way are you cool enough to pull of Clint.
Okay, so what name am I cool enough to pull off?
Umm, Gene.
See you later, Gene.
Bye, Gene.
It’s Clint! Clint!
What’s up with Gene?
So, you wore your nightie to dinner?
Oh, yeah. And uh, the best part though, when the uh, waiter spilled water down my back, I jumped up, and my boob popped out.
Oh my God!
Oh, no!
So?
So! Poetry? Susan’s gay! They’re being gay together!
Emily’s straight.
Oh, wake up!
Wow, Carol really messed you up!
Excuse me?
Look, I don’t know what you’re talking about, I am not a crazy, jealous person.
Huh.
What?
She’s totally right! When we were together, you got all freaked out about Mark and there was nothing going on.
This totally makes sense!
It does not!
Oh, sure it does! In high school, you weren’t jealous at all even though all your girlfriends were cheating on you!
All right, all right, so up until ‘92-93 he was very trusting, then ’94 hit, Carol left him and bamn! Paranoid city!
Absolutely! Absolutely!
This is so much fun!
This is not fun!
Look, all we’re trying to say is, don’t let what happened with Carol ruin what you got with Emily.
Yeah. The ’92 Ross wouldn’t.
Well, I still think I was right about that whole Mark thing.
What—yeah—what, y’know what? I hope Emily is a lesbian.
Drum roll.
Nah, you’re not tall enough to be a Mark, but you might make a good Barney.
All right look, am I serious, okay? Tomorrow at 3:30 I am going down to the courthouse.
You’re actually going through with this?

Hey, look, this name has been holding me back my entire life. Okay, it’s probably why kids picked on me in school, and why I never do well with women… So, as of 4 o’clock tomorrow, I’m either gonna be Mark Johnson or John Markson.
Yeah, but you have to keep the name too!
Okay. Thanks.
Okay!
You wanna hug it out?
Yeah!
Yay!
Yay!
Yay—oh—yay! Okay, I gotta go tell Frank and Alice! Right now!
Okay!
Bye, Pheebs!
Okay, bye!
Ha! Ha! Ha!
Nice luggage.
I was gonna say…
Hey!
Hi!
Hey! I missed you.
Oh, I missed you too.
Oh, so did I.
So, thank you for the delicious dinner.
You're welcome for a delicious dinner.
Hey what are you guys looking at?
Ross and the most beautiful girl in the world.
Yeah, come to papa.
I know!
Probably the only time I'll ever say this, but did you see the ass on her?
Yeah, so what is she, like a... like a spokesmodel, or an aerobics instructor, what?
Actually she's a paleontology doctoral candidate, specializing in the centazoic era.
Okay, but that's, like, the easiest era.
I've seen her at work, but I always figured, ah-huh? But, uh, I made her dinner. We had a great time. And we're going out again tomorrow.
Well maybe she and her friends are just having a contest to see who can bring home the biggest geek.
Fine by me; hope she wins.
Hi. You guys have any wrapping paper?
Oo! Is it for my birthday present?
Phebes, it was your birthday, like, months ago.
Yeah, but remember you said you ordered something special, and it just hasn't come yet?
Well, I have a call in about that.
'Kay.
Actually, this is for Kathy's birthday. It's an early edition of her favorite book.
Oh, The Velveteen Rabbit! Oh my God, when the boy's love makes the rabbit real!
Okay, but don't touch it, because you fingers have destructive oils.
Huh. Well, then you'd better keep it away from Ross's hair. So this is pretty rare. How did you get that?
Oh, it wasn't a big deal. I just went to a couple of bookstores, talked to a couple of dealers... called a couple of the author's grandchildren.
Oh, honey, that's so sweet.
Yeah, and what a great way to say, "I secretly love you, roommate's girlfriend!"
It doesn't say that. Does it?
How do you think it's gonna look when you get her something incredibly meaningful and expensive and her boyfriend Joey gives her an orange?
Okay, all right, I'll just uh, make sure that uh, Joey gets her something really great.
It's gotta be better than that book. Oo! Like a crossbow!
Oh my God! What happened?
Sixty guests.
So, uh, why did you have to turn it down?
Because I don't have the money or the equipment to handle something that big on such short notice. I mean there's no way.
I don't know.
There you go, that's the spirit! Okay! Now, if you need money, I will lend you money, but just get moving!
Really? Cause I'd need like $500 for all the food and the supplies and stuff.
Okay! It's worth it, if it will get you moving. You haven't worked in months.
Well, you're not working either.
Yes, but I'm doing this.
Yeah, that'd be great! Thank you!
Hey!
Hey.
Can I borrow the keys to your apartment?
Why?
You can pee here!
Ahahaha... haha.. yes I can, of course. Excuse me.
We've only been going out for a couple of weeks, do you think I gotta get her something?
Yeah!
Yes, you have to get her something, and it should be something really nice.
Oh, I know...
And not one of your coupons for an hour of "Joey Love."
Ooo, a crossword! Can I help?
No! I'm sorry, honey, it's just that last week I got all but three answers and I really want to finish a whole one without any help.
Fine. But you can't help me develop my new universal language.
Hey!
Hey, how'd it go?

Oh my God, it was the best funeral ever! I mean, everyone loved the food, and guess what? I even got another funeral for tomorrow—the dead-guy-from-today's best friend. I mean, it is like I am the official caterer for that accident!
Mon! I'm so happy for you!
I'll have one, please. Plus my money.

Oh. Well, I didn't realize that you needed it back right away. I mean, you told me to go and be a caterer. So I went. I beed. I mean, I... I used it to buy all this stuff. But look—I've got another job tomorrow, so I'll pay you back with the money I make from that.
Oh. Okay. Oo, sorry I acted like a bank.
Okay.
Um, would you like to come in?
Did homo-erectus hunt with wooden tools?
According to recent findings!
Mitzi is.....
My hamster. I hope she's okay, I haven't seen her in a while. Have a seat.
What?
Well, I do! Why don't we go back to my place, light a couple of candles, break open a box of Cinnamon Fruit Toasties, uh...
I'd rather not.
Oh, yeah, why not?
Okay, um, don't take this the wrong way, but your place kinda has a weird smell.
Oh, is everything in the car?
Yes. Did you settle the bill?
No. I hate this part.
No, that's not mine.
Oh, all right. Oh! Look what we almost took!
Excuse me, Mrs. Burkart? Well, we're all cleaned up in the kitchen.
Um, and, well there's the.. the the small matter of...
Just the matter of ...payment?
You know what we should all do? Go see a musical.
And you know which one we should see? The 1996 Tony award winner. Do you happen to know the name of that one?
I don't know... um, Grease?
Rent?
Yes! Rent!
Okay, so when do you want to go?
What? Oh, I'm sorry, I can't, I'm busy.
Yes, it is, at Office Max.
A pen.
It's two gifts in one. It's a pen that's also a clock! Huh?
Huh-huh! You can't give her that.
Why not?
Because she's not eleven! And it's not the seventh night of Hanukkah!
Okay, honey, what he means by that, is ...while this is a very nice gift, maybe it's just not something a boyfriend gives?
Sure it is! She needs a pen for work, she's writing, she turns it over.... "Whoa! It's time for my date with Joey!"
All right, look, look. What did... what did you get for Angela Delveccio for her birthday?
She didn't have a birthday while we were going out.
For three years?
All right. I will go out and I will try to find something for her, okay?
Thanks, man. And oh, while you're at it, could you get her a card?
Would you like me to write her a little poem as well?
Or... just get a card that has a poem already in it.
But Mon, you have to get our money!
Oh, Phoebe, she couldn't stop crying! With those thick glasses, her tears looked giant.
I know, it's tough. You know what the first thing I did after my mother's funeral was?
What?

Pay the caterer! Look, I've had a lot of jobs, okay, and there are some people who just always try to get out of paying. It's either, you know, "that massage wasn't long enough, or, "I don't recognize any of those songs," or, you know, "these sombreros aren't big enough. Bad little white girl!"
Okay. So what do you.... you think she's faking?
Well, it seems like there weren't any tears 'til you showed her the bill.
Phoebe, she sounded pretty upset to me.
She seems fine now.
So, you just left? Her place was really that bad?
You know how you throw your jacket on a chair at the end of the day?
Yeah.
Wow. Thanks. So, uh, what happened?
What do you mean? Nothing happened! I had to get out of there.
All right, so... next time, you take her to your place.
No, I tried that. She says it has a weird smell.
What kind of smell?
I don't know. Soap?
All right, listen, Ross... you like this girl, right?
Yeah.
You wanna see her again, right?
Yeah.
So you're gonna have to do it in the mess!
Yeah, okay you're right.
Yeah.
I mean, uh, who... who cares about a little sloppiness?
Yeah!
It's, uh... it's endearing, really.
Okay, all right. I just spent the entire afternoon looking for a present for Kathy that would be better than the rabbit.
Any luck?
All right, look. Why don't you just return the book, let Joey give her the clock pen, and you give her something worse than that. Like... a regular pen.
She's really going to love this, you know? The bottom line is I want her to have it, even if I don't get to be the one who gives it to her.
Aw, honey, that's so sweet.
Yeah? You don't think it's just pathetic?
Where?
Our place, the hall! I...
No, it's a book that's just a book, okay? It's an early edition of the Velveteen Rabbit. It was her favorite book as a kid. So, uh, just... let me know if she likes it, okay?
No, it came out to an even twenty.
Wow. That's almost as much as a new book.
You didn't get the money, did you?
Maybe I can try at intermission? Phoebe, come on... you know what? Let's just go!
Okay, Widow!
I'm gonna leave some cards here. Please think of us for you next event.
So you want to come inside?
Department of Sanitation?
It's me!
What?
Oh, Ross!
Wait! No! No! It's my hamster! It's Mitzi!
Oh my god! I'm so sorry, Cheryl. I must have freaked out.
I did it! Oh! I finished it! I did it all by myself! And there's nobody to hug!
Move!
Hey! Hey, you guys, I finished the crossword all by myself! Hug me!
Uh... yay!
Thanks!
Oh, that's great! Congratulations!
Thank you! Hey, how'd the catering go?
Oh, it was great! The widow wouldn't pay, so Phoebe yelled at her 'til she did.
Yeah. I'm a hard ass.
And I'm a wuss. And we should be partners.
Yeah. Hard Ass and Wuss. We could fight crime!
Wait a minute, Phoebe! We should be partners. We should be catering partners. I mean, think about it! You're not working right now, and we have such a great time together!
Okay!
I can cook and you can take care of the money.
Yeah. Oh! It'll be like I have a wife in the fifties!
Hey!
Hey, how'd it go? How'd she like the gift?
Oh, man, she loved it! She's over there showing Monica and Rachel right now.
Oh yeah? That's great!
Hey, listen, I gotta tell ya, I feel kinda bad taking credit for this, because man, am I gonna get a lot of credit for this!
Hey.
Hey!
Hey! Happy birthday.
Thank you!
Yeah, he did, look... look, it's right there on the counter! Ha-ho-ho!
Happy birthday! I'm sorry.
See, you think it's just a pen, but then you turn it over and it's also a clock.
Oh, yeah... yeah.
I'll be in in a minute.
Um, thank you for the gift.
Oh, uh, yeah... I just knew that sometimes when you're writing, you... you don't always know the exact time.
No, I... I didn't mean the pen. Thank you for the book.
Uh, the book?
The Velveteen Rabbit. I kinda have the feeling you had something to do with it.
What do you mean?
Well, uh, when Joey gave it to me, he said, "This is 'cause I know ya like Rabbits, and I know ya like cheese." Thanks. I love it. And I know how hard it must have been for you to find.
You must really like... Joey... to go to all that trouble for him.
Oh, yeah, he's my... he's my best friend.
Well....
Hi. Uh, you... you don't know me, I'm Monica Geller... Ross's sister.
Oh, yeah. Oh, you know, that's too bad that didn't work out.
Yeah. Anyway, he told me about your apartment. And, um, I couldn't sleep, thinking about it. So, uh, would it be okay if I cleaned it?
No?

You wanna finish this right now? All right, we get a deck of cards, high card wins. What do you say?
Fine, let’s do it.
Oh, I have cards!
Oh.
Oh, good.
Okay, you guys uh, you guys pick first
Okay.

Well, so, you-you’ll get a job here! I mean, I’m always hearing about uh, them foreigners coming in here and stealing American jobs; that could be you!

No, I can’t. I would, I really would, but my son is here; I can’t leave him. Isn’t—you don’t think there’s any way?
Ohh, I don’t think so. I mean it would be different if it was way into the future –and-and-and we were getting married or something.

Oh no, no, right I shouldn’t have said married. Uh, please don’t go freaky on me. I didn’t mean it. Well, I didn’t say it; I take it back!

Yes!

Oh my God!
Yes!

Yes.

The dark of night has disappeared!!

Sure.

I knooow.

Oh my God. You do?

For God sakes, it’s Rachel!

dialogue: Wait a minute, I see what's happening here. You're threatened.

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: What?

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: Yeah, I'm so good in this scene that I'm stealing focus from you. Well, rise to the challenge Tribianni 'cause I just raised the bar. Come join me up here!

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: You faked it? You couldn't have faked it!

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: Oh yes you can. You just make the faces and the noises.

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: Guys can fake it? Unbelievable. The one thing that's ours! Besides, why would you fake it when we're trying to have a baby?

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: That's actually why. Look, I'm starting a whole new career now, and I'm not saying that I don't want to have a baby, I'm just saying maybe we could wait a little while.

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: Like a month?

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: Or a year?

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: Really, you want to wait a year?

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: I really wanna have a baby.

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: Yeah, me too. Look, I'll just get my old job back.

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: No, I want you to have a job that you love. Not statistical analysis and data reconfiguration.

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: I quit and you learn what I do?

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: It's just, I think, there's never gonna be a right time to have a baby. I mean, now you're unemployed and in a little while you'll find a new job that'll keep you really busy. There's always gonna be a reason not to do this, but I think once the baby comes, forget about all those reasons.

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: I guess. It's always gonna be scary when we have a baby.

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: It's gonna be really scary. I mean, god. When we have a baby, there's gonna be so much that we're not able to control. I mean, the apartment's gonna be a mess, I won't have time to clean it. What if the baby gets into the ribbon drawer? Messes up all the ribbons?! What if there's no room for a ribbon drawer, because the baby's stuff takes up all the space!? Where will all the ribbons go!?!

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: Should we go make a baby right now before you change your mind?

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: Yes, please!

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: Oh, and I promise, I will not fake it this time.

filename: S09E11 Rachel Goes Back To Work.txt
dialogue: I wish I could say the same. I'm a little shook up!

dialogue: I'm not your brother.
Alright. Phoebe?
Okay, okay. If I were omnipotent for a day, I would want, um, world peace, no more hunger, good things for the rain-forest...And bigger boobs!
Yeah, see.. you took mine. Chandler, what about you?
Uh, if I were omnipotent for a day, I'd.. make myself omnipotent forever.
Hey Joey. Hi. Hey, buddy.
Hey, Joey, what would you do if you were omnipotent?
Probably kill myself!
..Excuse me?
Hey, if Little Joey's dead, then I got no reason to live!
Joey, uh- OMnipotent.
You are? Ross, I'm sorry..
How does she do that?
I cannot sleep in a public place.
Would you look at her? She is so peaceful.
It's okay, y'know, you just nodded off again.
What's going on with you?
I got no sleep last night!
Why?

My grandmother has this new boyfriend, and they're both kind of insecure in bed. Oh, and deaf. So they're constantly, like, having to reassure each other that they're having a good time. You have no idea how loud they are!
Well, if you want, you can stay with Rachel and me tonight.
Thanks.
...Ninety-five, ninety-six, ninety-seven. See, I told you! Less than a hundred steps from our place to here.
You got waaaay too much free time.
Happy birthday, pal!
Funny, my birthday was seven months ago.
So?
So, I'm guessing you had an extra ticket and couldn't decide which one of you got to bring a date?
Well, aren't we Mr. "The glass is half empty."
Oh my God, oh- is today the twentieth, October twentieth?
Oh, I was hoping you wouldn't remember.
Ohhh.
What's wrong with the twentieth?
Eleven days before Halloween.. all the good costumes are gone?
The hell with hockey, let's all do that!
What are you doing?
C'mon, Ross!
Alright, alright, maybe it'll take my mind off it. Do you promise to buy me a big thumb finger?
You got it.
Look-look-look-look-look, my first pay check! Look at the window, there's my name! Hi, me!
I remember the day I got my first pay check. There was a cave in in one of the mines, and eight people were killed.
Wow, you worked in a mine?
I worked in a Dairy Queen, why?
Oh, you're fine, yeah, for a first job.
You can totally, totally live on this.
Yeah, yeah.
Oh, by the way, great service tonight.
Oh! Yeah!
Oh my God! (Rachel, Leslie, Kiki, and Joanne all scream and hug each other.
What are you guys doing here?
Well, we were in the city shopping, and your mom said you work here, aaand it's true!
Look at you in the apron. You look like you're in a play.
I know. I know! I'm a duplex.
We'll take a brief time out while Messier stops to look at some women's shoes.
What?
Peach pit.
Yes, Bunny?
-Peaches?
Actually, nectarines, but basically...
So c'mon, you guys, tell me all the dirt!
Well, the biggest news is still you dumping Barry at the altar!
Alright. Let's talk reality for a second.
Okay.
When are you coming home?
What? Guys, I'm not.
C'mon, this is us.
I'm not! This is what I'm doing now. I've got this job-
Waitressing?

Okay, I'm not just waitressing. I'm.. I, um... I write the specials on the specials board, and, uh... and I, uh... I take the uh dead flowers out of the vase... Oh, and, um, sometimes Artelle lets me put the little chocolate blobbies on the cookies.
Well. Your mom didn't tell us about the blobbies.
What's that?
Weeeell, it's rum, and-
Ooh! Ooh! And I brought Operation! But, um, I lost the tweezers, so we can't operate. But we can prep the guy!
Uh, Rach, it's the Visa card people.
Oh, God, ask them what they want.
But I haven't used my card in weeks!
That is the unusual activity. Look, they just wanna see if you're okay.

They wanna know if I'm okay. Okay.. they wanna know if I'm okay, okay, let's see. Well, let's see, the FICA guys took all my money, everyone I know is either getting married, or getting promoted, or getting pregnant, and I'm getting coffee! And it's not even for me! So if that sounds like I'm okay, okay, then you can tell them I'm okay, okay?
What? There was ice there that night with Carol? Plastic seats? Four thousand angry Pittsburgh fans?
No, actually I was just saying it looks like we're not sitting together. But now you mention it, there was ice there that night... It was the first frost...
C'mon, sit. Just sit down, sit.
You should feel great about yourself! You're doing this amazing independence thing!
Monica, what is so amazing? I gave up, like, everything. And for what?
You are just like Jack.
...Jack from downstairs?
No, Jack and the Beanstalk.
Ah, the other Jack.

Yeah, right! See, he gave up something, but then he got those magic beans. And then he woke up, and there was this, this big plant outside his window, full of possibilities and stuff.. And he lived in a village, and you live in the Village..
Okay, but Pheebs, Pheebs, Jack gave up a cow, I gave up an orthodontist. Okay, I-I-I know, I know I didn't love him-
Oh, see, Jack did love the cow.
But see, it was a plan. Y'know, it was clear. It was figured out, and now everything's just kinda like...
Floopy?
Yeah.
So what, you're not the only one. I mean, half the time we don't know where we're going. You've just gotta figure at some point it's all gonna come together, and it's just gonna be... un-floopy.
Oh, like that's a word.
Okay, but Monica, what if- what if it doesn't come together?
...Pheebs?
Oh, well... 'cause.... you just... I don't like this question.
Okay, see, see, you guys, what if we don't get magic beans? I mean, what if all we've got are.. beans?
Get him! GET HIM! Get him! Get- YESSS! Not laughing now, are ya pal!
Pass it! Pass it!
He's open!
Shoot! Shoot! Shoot!
Hey, look, we're on that TV thing!
Well, you'll have to wait your turn.
Well, how long do you think it'll be?
I'm so sorry, you guys. I didn't mean to bring you down.
Phoebe?
What?
Do you have a plan?
I don't even have a 'pl'.
Wait, was this a-a small mediterranean guy with curiously intelligent good looks?
Was he wearing a stunning blue suit?
And-and a power tie?
Uh, Pheebs? Who's George Snuffalopagus?
Big Bird's friend.
I see pizza!
Hello? Who are we spying on?
White House adviser? Clinton's campaign guy? The one with the great hair, sexy smile, really cute butt?
Oh, him, the little guy? Oh, I love him!
Ooh, wait.. wait, I see a woman.
Please tell me it's his mother.
Definitely not his mother.
Oh, no...
Light still out?
Yeah.
Oh. Maybe they're- napping.
Oh please, they're having sex.
So, whaddya think George is like?
I think he's shy.
Yeah?
Yeah. I think you have to draw him out. And then- when you do- he's a preppy animal.
I remember the moonlight coming through the window- and her face had the most incredible glow.
Yes, the moon, the glow, the magical feeling, you did this part- Could I get some painkillers over here, please?
He's right, enough, already. What is the big deal about today? So you slept with her for the first time, so what? You slept with her for seven years after that.
Look, it's just a little more complicated...
Well, what? What? What is it? That she left you? That she likes women? That she left you for another woman that likes women?
Little louder, okay, I think there's a man on the twelfth floor in a coma that didn't quite hear you...
Then what?
What?
It was my first time.
Whoah, boy, hockey was a big mistake! There was a whole bunch of stuff we could've done tonight!
Okay. Okay, I got one. Do you remember that vegetarian pate that I made that you loved so much?
Uh-huh.
Well, unless goose is a vegetable...ha haaaah!
Oh! Oh! Oh! Okay, fine, fine. Now I don't feel so bad about sleeping with Jason Hurley.
What?! You slept with Jason?
You'd already broken up.
How long?
A couple hours.
Oh, that's nice!
Excuse me?!
Really. Well, at least 'big girls' don't pee in their pants in seventh grade!
There he is! There he is!
Where?
Right- where we've been looking all night!
He is so cute!
Oh, George, baby, drop the towel!
Man. Can you believe he's only had sex with one woman?
I think it's great. Y'know, it's sweet, it's romantic...
Really?
Hey, buddy.
Oh, I thought you were great in Silence of the Lambs. Oh come on, admit it! All things considered, you had fun tonight.
Fun? Where was the fun? Tell me specifically, which part was the fun part? Where's my puck?
Oh, ah- the kid has it.
You gotta do it, man.
No.
'Yes', how about. C'mere. Gimme!
Hey! Hey! No rough holding in my ER!
...Now that was fun.
Could've played Monopoly, but nooooo.
Hello? Oh, uh, Rachel, it's the Visa card people.
Oh, okay. Will you take my place?
Green. To the green.

My God, I can’t believe this! I mean I knew that mom and dad were invited, but I thought that was it! I mean from the ages 7 to 9 Frannie and I were inseparable!
Well, maybe since the age of 9, Frannie’s made some new friends.
Well l-look okay, it’s probably just a mistake. Let me call Aunt Sheryl okay? Maybe you are invited and the invitation just got lost in the mail.

Yeah, well you call her and tell her that y’know when we were kids her precious little Frannie tried to undress me several times, okay? And if I hadn’t have stopped her, there probably wouldn’t even be a wedding to go too.

Hey, you can cancel plans with friends if there is the possibility for sex!
Phoebe he’s right, that is the rule.
Wow! I’m so sorry; I had no idea it would bother you this much.
Well, it does.
Okay, you wore me down.
Hey Joe, while you’re over there how about another beer for the Ross-A-Tron?
Hi!

Well I’ve forgotten what it tastes like okay?!

Good idea. Where do you want to go to lunch?
Awww! Mel Torme died.

Hey.

Well yeah, but she doesn’t know that. I mean, the last time she saw you-you would’ve turned one of those little wedding chairs into kindling.

Oh what’s the big deal?! I wasn’t even invited to the ceremony, just the reception. And-and y’know what? If it makes you feel any better, Joan and I will just make an appearance and then, and then we’ll-we’ll leave early as a sign of protest.
Joan?
Yeah, Joan Tedeski my date. She’s an assistant professor in the Linguistics department. Tall, very beautiful, and despite what some people say, not broad backed!
Wait a minute, you got Ross Gellar and guest?! I wasn’t invited and you got "and guest?!"
Uh-uh, excuse me, I do have to interrupt on Ross’s behalf. I-I think the rule applies here y’know, since she has a chance to get on broad back…
Wait a minute, y’know, you’re bringing me!
What? I can’t cancel on Joan!
Why not?!
Bec—Did you not hear me?! She’s an assistant professor in the Linguistics department, okay? They’re wild! Why do you want to come anyway?
Because! She’s my cousin. I mean, we grew up together! We’re family y’know? Well that’s important to me.
Aww that’s nice. Family should be there, huh? This is her wedding, happiest day of her life.
Well, thank you for lunch.
What? Wait a minute, I didn’t pay, I thought you paid!

No that could kill her.
Well, we don’t want that.
No so we’re protecting her.
But we should take it.
But we should move quick.
Why?
Because I think I just heard her moving around in there.
David who?
David the scientist guy, David that I was in love with, David who went to Russia and broke my heart David!
Oh, you say someone’s name enough, they turn around.
Phoebe?
Yeah, I’m just, I’m just in town for a conference. Umm, God you look phenomenal!
Well… Yeah. You look great too. Did you get a haircut?
Yeah. Well I-I got like thirty of them.
Yeah.
Umm, look I-I-I got a confession to make…
Uh-huh.

Uh, I-I-I was hoping to run into you here. I didn’t know whether I should call or not, y’know I-I was only in town for a few days. And y’know, I didn’t want to intrude on your life or-or anything like that, but I-I really wanted to see you and—but I didn’t know if you wanted to see me.
Well, of course I would want to see you. I…I think about you all the time.
Really? Because I think about you all the time.
Really?
I mean, there’s a statue in Minsk…
Uh-huh.
That reminds me of you so much, I mean umm, it-it’s actually of Lenin. But, y’know at certain angles…
Yeah.
Umm, anyway…Do you want to have dinner tonight?
I can’t. I can’t believe I have plans, I can’t. Can you do it tomorrow night though?
Uh no, I have to go in a few hours. I have to be on the red-eye. Well listen, y’know, next time you’re in Minsk umm…
Phoebe, can I talk to you for a second?
What are you doing?
Well, I have plans with Joey tonight.
So! He’ll understand!

No he won’t. And that’s not even the point! Monica, I made a whole speech about you do not cancel plans with friends! And now y’know what? Just because, potentially, the love of my life comes back from Russia just for one night, I-I should change my beliefs?! I should change beliefs! No! No! No, if I don’t have my principles, I don’t have anything!
God, you are so strong.
Or! I should rush through dinner with Joey and I can meet David at 9:00!
I’m full, and yet I know if I stop eating this, I’ll regret it.
Hey!
What are you doing tonight?
Oh really? Uh, Monica said she had a date at 9:00.
What?! Tonight?!
That’s what Monica said.
After she gave me that big speech?! She goes and makes a date with a guy on the same night she has plans with me? I think she’s trying to pull a fast one on Big Daddy!
I’m Monica Gellar. Who do you know the bride and groom?
Used to work with her. Used to! I’m a relative and I didn’t get invited! A blood relative! Blood!!
Okay, you’re fine.
Hey!
Yes! I will have the green salad, umm the house salad, and water’s fine.
Okay.
Yeah, this slow roasted salmon, just how slow are we talkin’ here?
Ohh, then no. Maybe I should hear those specials again.
Huh?
You were right before. I mean, friends are so important.
Y’know-y’know what I really want?
What?
Is to have a long, long talk. Y’know? Get Joey out on the open road and really open him up.
Yes! I will have the lobster ravioli.
God Joey, this is taking forever!
What’s the rush? What?
W-w—I just—it’s that—I have—y’know I have-I have an appointment. And it’s very important.
Whoa-whoa, what is it?
Well… It’s a date.
A date?! No, no Pheebs you-you must be mistaken, because I know you wouldn’t schedule a date on the same night you have plans with a friend!
Come on Joey, don’t make me feel badly about this.
No, I’m gonna!! That’s right! Yeah, you made me feel really guilty about goin’ out with that girl! Like-like-like I did something terrible to you! And now Pheebs, you’re doing the same thing!
That—It’s not the same thing! This is totally different! This is with David! Remember David, the scientist guy? Okay, he’s very special to me.
Okay, well my girl from the other night was special. She was a scientist too!
She was?
Well, she graduated from high school!
Fine!
Yeah!
Fine!
Hey!
Hey! Oh, I was just about to leave. I-I-I-I didn’t think you were coming.
Oh, I wouldn’t miss this.
Are you eating the cheesecake without me?!

Oh, what are you going to do?! Are you gonna go run tell Monica?! Are you gonna tell Joey?! No! Because then you will have to tell them what we did! We are desert stealers! We are living outside the law!
What?! What?!
Oh yes!
Wait a minute!
Oh yes!
Oh no-no-no-no-no, no you don’t!
Oh yes! Oh yes!
You think I trust you with it?! No! We’re gonna split it! You take half and I take half!
Well that’s not fair, you’ve already had some!
What? Oh, well then y’know what? I think Monica would be very interested to know that you called her cheesecake dry and mealy.
What do we use to split it?
Oh for God sake just pick a piece!
Okay, you gotta give me some of your piece.
Oh, hey Aunt Millie.
Now wait a minute, you be nice! All right? I didn’t bring you here so you can ambush her.
Frannie was the one who found your Playboys and showed them to mom.
Am I doing here? Why? Surprised to see me? Ross brought me. How do you like that?!
I believe you know my husband.
So it’s really a question of who could you have possibly done.
Oh, I hate this but I-I-I have to go. I-I can’t miss my flight.
Are you sure? I’ll bet there’s another flight to Minsk in like…
That’s really beautiful. What does it mean?
Please, clean my beakers. I don’t get out of the lab much.
That’s good. I got to admit, I thought it was something else.
Yeah, I… Well I really actually wanted to say umm, that, but um, I figured I probably shouldn’t because y’know, I…have to leave.
You’re right! You’re right. Don’t say it.
I-I do though.
Hey, y’know you could always visit him.
Oh right, like they’re gonna let me have a passport.
Anything I can do? Whatever you need.
I can give it a shot.
Oh! Yay! Look! There’s a piece that doesn’t have floor on it!
Stick to your side!
Hey, come on now!
Oh wait I forgot my wrap.
Well…

Okay, come here! Come here.

Okay.

Okay.

Oop!
Well, it’s like that old saying, have some sex, eat some cake.
Who the hell are you?!
Look, I got to apologize on the behalf of Carl.
Who the hell is Carl?!
Oh, did I not mention? Carl is a guy I hired to be my identical twin for a medical research project.
Y’know sometimes the good ideas are just right in front of you, aren’t they?

Yeah, he’s the reason I didn’t get that big Minute Maid commercial a couple of years ago remember? We were supposed to be brothers, but he messed it up.
Pat Sajak?
Yep!
Alex Trebek?
Oh, of course!
Chuck Woolery?
Definitely! Phoebe, you will not find a single game show host, who’s ass I cannot kick.

Say we are unagi!
It’s not something you are! It’s something you have!

Damnit Carl!
